'''Lothian''' is one of the eight [[Scottish Parliament constituencies and regions|electoral regions]] of the [[Scottish Parliament]].  Nine of the parliament's 73[[first past the post]] [[Scottish Parliament constituencies and regions|constituencies]] are sub-divisions of the region and it elects seven of the 56 [[additional member system (Scottish Parliament)|additional-member]] [[Member of the Scottish Parliament|Members of the Scottish Parliament (MSPs)]]. Thus it elects a total of 16 MSPs. 

The West Scotland was created as a result of the [[First Periodic Review of Scottish Parliament Boundaries]] and largely replaced the 
[[Lothians (Scottish Parliament electoral region)|Lothians]] region.<ref>http://www.bcomm-scotland.gov.uk/1st_holyrood/1st_holyrood.asp</ref>

